    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, maintained to an exacting standard. This specimen features the original 13B-REW rotary engine, exhibiting exceptional compression results and a cooling system upgraded with a dual-pass aluminum radiator to ensure thermal stability. The sequential twin-turbocharger setup operates with surgical precision, providing a linear torque curve without the typical vacuum-actuation lag. The chassis is structurally pristine, retaining its factory 50/50 weight distribution with an untouched double-wishbone suspension and zero oxidation on the undercarriage components. Shifting is executed via a precise short-throw five-speed manual gearbox paired with a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. Every panel bears the original VIN sticker, and the interior plastics remain supple with no UV-induced embrittlement. This is a rare, turn-key opportunity for the technical purist.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 43
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
